As used in KRS 138.510 to 138.550:
"Advanced deposit account wagering" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Advanced deposit account wagering license" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Association" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Commission" means the Kentucky Horse Racing Commission;
"Daily average live handle" means:
The handle from wagers made at a track on live racing during the fiscal year, excluding amounts wagered:
At a receiving track;
At a simulcast facility;
On telephone account wagering;
Through advance deposit account wagering;
At a track participating as a receiving track or simulcast facility displaying simulcasts and conducting interstate wagering as permitted by KRS 230.3771 and 230.3773; and
Beginning April 1, 2014, on historical horse races; divided by:
The total number of days that live racing was conducted at the track during the fiscal year;
"Department" means the Department of Revenue;
"Fiscal year" means a time frame beginning 12:01 a.m. July 1, and ending 12 midnight June 30;
"Handle" means total wagers made on a race;
"Historical horse race" means any horse race that:
Was previously run at a licensed pari-mutuel facility in the United States;
Concluded with official results; and
Concluded without scratches, disqualifications, or dead-heat finishes.
As used in this subsection, the terms "pari-mutuel," "scratch," "disqualification," and "dead heat" have the same meaning as established by the commission pursuant to an administrative regulation promulgated under KRS Chapter 13A;
"Host track" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Interstate wagering" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Intertrack wagering" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Kentucky resident" means:
An individual domiciled within this state;
An individual who maintains a place of abode in this state and spends, in the aggregate, more than one hundred eighty-three (183) days of the taxable year in this state; or
An individual who lists a Kentucky address as his or her principal place of residence when applying for an account to participate in advance deposit account wagering;
"Receiving track" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Simulcast facility" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210;
"Takeout" means that portion of the handle which is distributed to persons other than those making wagers;
"Telephone account wagering" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210; and
"Track" has the same meaning as in KRS 230.210.
